headline: Gilead’s HIV Treatments Could Face Headwinds. Why the Stock Will Still Rise.
summary: Gilead Sciences  stock has room to climb, and investors shouldn’t overlook the company’s impressive record in navigating HIV policy, Citi Research says.  Analysts led by Geoff Meacham reiterated a Buy rating on the shares with a $125 price target in a note Wednesday.  With Gilead up 1.2% to $109.23 on Wednesday, the price target suggests potential upside of 14%.
